Script Purpose; 
	 This script crates a new database named ‘DataWarehouse’ after checking if it already exits. If the database exist, it is dropped and recreated. Additionally, the script sets up three schemas within the database;  ‘bronze’ ‘silver’ and ‘gold’

WARNING;
Running this scipt will drop the entire ‘DataWareouse’ database if it exists. All data in the database will be permanently deleted. Proceed with caution and ensure you have proper backups before running this scipt


--Create Database 'DataWarehouse'
USE master;

--Drop and recreate the 'Datawarehouse; database
IF EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM sys.databases WHERE name = 'DataWarehouse')
BEGIN
	ALTER DATABASE DataWarehouse SET SINGLE_USER WITH ROLLBACK IMMEDIATE;
	DROP DATABASE DataWarehouse

CREATE DATABASE dataWarehouse;

USE DataWarehouse;

--the go command is a seperator that tells sql to execute completely before next command
CREATE SCHEMA bronze;
GO
CREATE SCHEMA silver;
go
CREATE SCHEMA gold;
go
